"text":"Jan. 12, 1983","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/2369"},"text":"96 Stat. 2369","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/369/dA/tVII/s711/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–369, div. A, title VII, § 711(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", (3)(B), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-07-18"},"text":"July 18, 1984","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/98/942"},"text":"98 Stat. 942","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/514/tXVIII/s1875/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–514, title XVIII, § 1875(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-10-22"},"text":"Oct. 22, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/2894"},"text":"100 Stat. 2894","children":[],"tail":", related to rules for application of minimum tax for tax preferences, prior to the general revision of this part by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/514/s701/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–514, § 701(a)","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id41241d95-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2018—Subsec. (a)(2)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/141"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–141","children":[],"tail":" substituted “461(k)” for “461(j)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2017—Subsec. (a)(3), (4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/97"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–97","children":[],"tail":" redesignated par. (4) as (3) and struck out former par. (3). Prior to amendment, text of par. (3) read as follows: “For purposes of paragraph (1), a personal service corporation (within the meaning of section 469(j)(2)) shall be treated as a taxpayer other than a corporation.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2014—Subsec. (a)(2)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/295/s221/a/58/E"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–295, § 221(a)(58)(E)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “section 461(j)” for “section 464(c)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/295/s221/a/60/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–295, § 221(a)(60)(B)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “and” at end of par. (1), redesignated par. (3) as (2) and struck out former par. (2) which read as follows: “the provisions of section 469(m) (relating to phase-in of disallowance) shall not apply, and”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1988—Subsec. (a)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/647/s1007/d/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–647, § 1007(d)(1)","children":[],"tail":", struck out “(as modified by section 461(i)(4)(A))” after “section 464(c)” in subpar. (A) and substituted “section 469(c)” for “section 469(d), without regard to paragraph (1)(B) thereof” in subpar. (B)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/647/s1007/d/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–647, § 1007(d)(2)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “469(j)(2)” for “469(g)(1)(C)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/647/s1007/d/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–647, § 1007(d)(3)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (4)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/647/s1007/d/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–647, § 1007(d)(4)","children":[],"tail":", added pars. (1) to (3) and struck out former pars. (1) to (3) which read as follows:"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(1) the adjustments of section 56 shall apply,","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(2) any deduction to the extent such deduction is an item of tax preference under secti